title: Why Microsoft Stock Popped Today
description: Shares of Microsoft (NASDAQ: MSFT) climbed more than 4% on Tuesday after the software giant announced some highly anticipated, AI-powered upgrades to its web browser and search tools.  Microsoft is adding a new chat box to its Bing homepage.  The new AI-driven tool can provide more complete and relevant answers than traditional search engines, according to Microsoft.

title: Hot Stocks: BIDU gets AI boost; OSH takeover chatter; FISV climbs on earnings; CHGG falls
description: BIDU led a list of big-name stocks that rallied on AI hopes. OSH jumped on takeover chatter. FISV rose on earnings news. CHGG dropped on its quarterly report.

title: Markets Rise on Powell's Inflation Comments
description: U.S. equities posted gains on Feb. 7 after Fed Chair Jerome Powell said that inflation was easing but noted that rate hikes would continue if needed.
